# Dagger's generated client — /dagger.gen.go and /internal/dagger — is COMMITTED,
# not ignored. It is the only importer of this module's requirements, so where it
# does not exist `go mod tidy` finds every one of them unused and empties go.mod
# (#40). Committing it is also what lets plain Go tooling — go build, go vet,
# gopls — work in here on a fresh checkout with no Dagger CLI installed.
#
# The `!` lines are load-bearing twice over.
#
# They say what we mean: these paths are not ignored, so a client file that is
# entirely *new* — adding a module dependency generates one — is visible to
# `git add` rather than silently absent from the commit.
#
# And they hold off `dagger develop`, which re-appends any of its default ignore
# entries it cannot find in this file. Delete them and the next run re-arms the
# trap. If CI's `codegen` job reports this file as modified, that is what
# happened.

/.env

!/dagger.gen.go
!/internal/dagger
!/internal/telemetry
